caption: Delicous babaganoush, tender lamb kabobs, wonderful Turkish coffee. Will absolutely return.

We arrived little earlier and felt very safe because there was no guest inside the restaurant. The food was greater than I expected and the staff was also kind. They put some almonds on the white rice, and put lots of mushrooms on the salmon.
Our hotel recommended this restaurant on a quick visit to the DC area.  We found the food to be really great and the owner/manager treated us with much kindness. We will definitely be back soon!

I ordered takeout recently, and I have to say as an Egyptian, this food made me so happy.  So many restaurants claim to have Lebanese cuisine, but this is one of the few places that is even close to the real thing.  I look forward to ordering from them again soon.
The service is always swift, good atmosphere, helpful employees. Will visit again when I get in the area.

Our family has been going to Bacchus for over 20 years. One side of our family descends from Lebanon. Therefore, we grew up eating authentic Lebanese cuisine in our homes.  Bacchus of Lebanon is a truly authentic experience. Inside you'll find a peaceful, cozy, atmosphere.  Outside patio seating near the fountain transports you to the Mediterranean. The food is exceptional. The service always superb. The owner, Zaid, provides a truly old-fashioned, personal, customer service experience. Highly recommend it.

This is one of my favorite restaurants.  Their spices served with pita at the beginning of the meal are absolutely scrumptious.  I could dine on that alone.  Everything is prepared beautifully and the seasonings are just perfect.  I have not had anything I didn't like.  Please support this awesome restaurant with take-out during these awful times.  It would be sad to see this restaurant have to close.
Amazing food and service!
Good food and outdoor seating..

BACCHUS of Lebanon is a fine dining experience. The quality of the food is very good and the menu is varied and should appeal to anyone. The preparation of the dishes is superior to many restaurants in a higher price range.The service is attentive and very professional. This has been the standard I have observed over several visits. Recently dined outside on patio, August 2020. Has maintained its quality of food and service, even in these difficult times.

I've been dining at Bacchus for years and have always liked the food. My expectations for their take-away service was high. What a huge disappointment!  First, my order did not include one of the appetizers which my son ordered. Second the tabouli salad was *very old* and not very tasty. Third, most of the very expensive main dishes had only 4-5 pieces of meat or fish and were mostly overcooked. It was as if we were given leftovers? The sauce was extremely salty to the point that no one ate it.  I will not be returning for dine-in or take away again.

I’m Arab and rarely recommend a Middle Eastern restaurant. This one is fantastic! Lebanese owned. My favorite dishes are the fettas (meat over pita bread crumbs with a tangy, yogurt garlic sauce) especially the lamb, and the malfouf (cabbage rolls stuffed with rice and minced beef in a light tomato sauce). But everything I’ve had there is wonderful. And they have spacious outdoor seating in the shade, which is great for these times. Can’t recommend enough!

We have been coming here as far back as I can remember. Friendly staff, great service, and amazing food every time. The patio is beautiful with a serene waterfall, always an excellent meal, no better Lebanese food in the entire DMV!

I have been eating at this restaurant for a very long time now and I love everything about it. Being of Lebanese heritage Bacchus is the best as it gets. Hands down the best Lebanese food in the DMV!!

It's been a long time since we went out to eat due to COVID-19 restrictions. This was an excellent choice for us to try. The restaurant was clean and they provided hand sanitizer at each table. We ordered a mix of vegetarian and non-vegetarian food. The service and food quality were both excellent. The Harissa sauce was simply superb.  We will absolutely visit this restaurant again as the current restrictions ease.
Bacchus of Lebanon new looks!!

The wait staff was fine. I got a Sauvignon Blanc when I ordered a Pinot Grisio. That wasn't a big deal. Then we ordered 3 small plates. The cauliflower was bland. The warm hummus was mediocre and not warm. The baba ghanoush was basically shredded eggplant in hummus topped with tomatoes and parsley. The pita was extremely dry to the point where it would crack. The best part about my experience is that I didn't order more food.

Disappointed in myself for never dining here before. I'm a big fan of Lebanese and Mediterranean food. Stopped by recently and had everything from the beef and swordfish platter, hommos, fried eggplant, bacchus shrimp, shish taouk with some friends. Everything here was delicious. We loved the lamb and swordfish. The fish itself was cooked so well we all thought it was meat. The sabanegh bel zeit with the bread and dipping oil had some great texture. They have an extensive wine menu which is perfect with all of this delicious food. The staff had on gloves and masks. Seats were 6 ft apart and they had hand sanitizer every where throughout the restaurant. My friends and I really enjoyed our experience here. Prices are reasonable and we left completely stuffed. I'll definitely be back to try their other speciality items and their konafah

The most flavorful Lebanese food I've had. And great customer service. My server was very attentive and gave a complimentary dessert that was also outstanding! The ambiance is relaxing and pleasing to the eye. I will be returning.

Bacchus of Lebanon is one of the best Middle Eastern restaurants in the region. I have been going there for probably 25 years and have never had anything but a great meal. The service is wonderful, accommodating and makes you feel like you're home.

I ordered dinner for pick up, I wasn’t sure about the quality of the food so I decided to go with shawarma,  falafel, and kunafeh for dessert, nothing fancy. The food was very delicious, everything  was really well cooked and so tasty. I didn’t know their porch was open, dinner would’ve been much yummier! Next time😉
We had a great time dining outdoors at Bacchus earlier this week. Timo, the server, was excellent. Our food was delicious. Will be back soon!

This is no doubt one of the tastiest restaurants in the area. Every time I come there I am incredibly happy. They preserve their high  standard service and the topmost level of meals  they offer. You are always happy with this place. Very  recommended.
The food and service here is excellent!

This restaurant is my first choice site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. when  I I need a delicious dinner, this is the place that comes instantly to my mind. very good and varied  food and a rich cuisine.courteous staff, and great mood. Not less important, the expence is affordable. I tell about this place with no hesitation.
Very good restaurant. Food was well prepared and tasty. Staff was friendly and attentive. Tight seating inside and can be very loud.
This place is worth a try. They serve large portions for fair prices. Consistently well organized and with good mood. Will come back again.

Best place I ate at in the area.  Had a select of appetizers many of which where vegetarian and some that where not.  The food was spiced well and had a nice vinegar balance.  Soup was perfect for the cold day.  I cannot speak highly enough of the servers, polite and efficient!

Lebanese restaurant first tome trying it. The place is nice, atmosphere and the decoration! I went there with group of 10 ppl. ordered combination bacchus (1 chicken kabob and 1 lamb over rice) which was really good the chicken was moist not dry. Very one enjoyed their food! At the end of our meals the restaurant offered a complimentary rice pudding and baklava soo tasty and fresh. The only complain the food took forever to come out.will definitely come back
Continually raises the bar on well prepared and tasty dishes. For great Mediterranean and Lebanese food, this is the place!

Wow!  I'm not sure where to even begin -- probably  the moment when our team stepped off our charter bus to get the most amazIng whiff of grilled Lebanese delicacies that fill the sidewalk.  Truth is the aroma only got better once we went inside and found tabouleh, falafel, hummus and baba ghanoush waiting for us.  Our team of 25 high school upperclassmen devoured the appetizers only to be floored by the bountiful spread of Kafka, and grilled chicken set upon a bed of aromatic rice with grilled onions and tomatoes.  Spectacular!  As if that was not enough, the lightest limoncello custard was graciously served to round out our "meal of the Gods!"  Mixed with the stunning ambience all around you, this restaurant is a MUST TRY if you are ever in Bethesda! Zaid is the most gracious manager and purveyor of incredible food that we have ever had on our team's travels....It has been an honor getting to know him for 5+ years.  His staff is equally accommodating and whether it's a casual Thursday evening, like tonight, or a memorable family occasion that you are celebrating, you've got to try Bacchus of Lebanon!  Like us from Pittsburgh, you will be a fan for life....
I can eat here every day! Authentic Lebanese cuisine.
Great food and very friendly service even though they were understaffed. The pita bread and olive oil dip are simply amazing. A bit pricy but it is Bethesda after all.

Mostly good service and good food in a pleasant atmosphere. I asked about the hot tea selection but the waiter forgot to bring me the box with the tea choices as he said he would. Otherwise very attentive service. As with most commercial Lebanese restaurants and delis, I thought the food was over salted. But this seems to be the norm. I liked the zataar and olive oil dip for the pita bread, as well as the mint and cucumber yogurt sauce. The romain lettuce for the tabouleh was very fresh. No raw kibbee here, and the grape leaves and cabbage rolls had "meat" in them. I thought $42 for a mediocre bottle of Reisling was pricey. I would return next time I am in the area.

This is our go to restaurant. We come at least once a week if not twice. The waiters make you feel at home. The food is the best on the block. There's so much variety that we're always trying something different and loving it. It's also very kid friendly.
The best lamb I have eaten in a restaurant in my life!

This place is nice. It is beautifully decorated and the taste is authentic and delicious. Quick and wonderful service. I tried their Lamb Mechwi that’s marinated in their special house spice, garlic and fresh herb with their stuffed grape leave. I really enjoyed my time at this restaurant.
Excellent food with excellent staff. Family friendly with authentic Lebanese food. I often find myself asking why I go anywhere else.
The best mideteranin food ever! Went there 2 days in a row.  Loved it.
Food was delicious. They serve complimentary hot bread with a zaatar and olive oil dip. Yumm!!

This is one of the few authentic Lebanese restaurants in the area, which is a relief to find!  It's a strangely upscale atmosphere, especially when ordering foods that I would expect at more modest settings, like lubia b'zeit (string beans in oil), or mujadara (lentils on rice with caramelized onions).  Even though I don't care for fancy restaurants, I still eat here, because everything they do is well spiced, tenderly cooked, and somehow both indulgent and light.  If you have even a passing interest in Mediterranean food, definitely give Bacchusa try.
Excellent authentic Lebanese dishes.
This is one of the best Lebanese restaurants I have been to in this country.  Very authentic and a great variety of dishes. The staff is very nice and professional.

One of my family's favorite restaurants. The owner is a wonderful host, and always adds to the enjoyment of our meal. Great place for tapas or full entrees. You must try the hummus, bacchus shrimp, and Arayess small plates.

The Bacchus of Lebanon is an absolutely wondrous experience. First of all, the food that is offered at this restaurant is packed with wonderful flavors - from their Chicken Schwarma down to their freshly picked mint garnish. The service offered by this establishment is nothing short of impeccable either. If you're nearby, this is an establishment that you must visit.
My favorite Lebanese restaurant
Very mediocre taste
Tender lamb!
I was disappointed. The hummus was ok. The falafel was not great. The shwarma was good.
Excellent Mediterranean cuisine.

I took my wife and kids out last night. Had a great time! Food is consistently good. The lamb is amazing and a good selection of Lebanese wine. Friendly staff. Please be patient - the staff is a little short handed sometimes but everyone is hustling and dedicated. Overall, one of the better, affordable, restaurants in Bethesda.

Staff kept on trying to Rush us. First he came asking to collect the plates while I was still eating. Secondly another staff “Timo” gave us a very rude approach from the moment we walked. If he had a bad day, he Should have just stayed at home. I am give 1 star because the food was great and customer service was terrible!
Wonderful Lebonese dishes. A long-standing favorite in Bethesda. Outside dining also available.
Just wonderful food
Excellent food, courteous and friendly staff, great ambience. Slow service.
Best restaurant in DC

Patio is fantastic. Food was all quite good. Service was prompt. Tip: space out your orders or request that they are brought in courses, we ordered a dinner of mezze plates and they all came at once. Critical feedback - when server perfume is too strong it detracts from the food.
Exquisite food, amazing service & ambience; highly recommend to anyone seeking a flavorful experience!
(Translated by Google) Good service, excellent food and fast food!  (Original) Buena atención , comida excelente y sirven la comida rapido!!
Food was great, nice, classy atmosphere. Bit on the expensive side, but you get what you pay for!
Good food Good service Little pricey
The food was so nice and the service were great. I would like to come back!
I love this place! A great place to share a few entrees and the Shawarma is amazing! Don't miss out on it.

My wife and I were looking forward to celebrating our first year wedding anniversary at Bacchus of Lebanon until they cancelled our reservation the day of because of a private function. That isn't how reservations work.
Best Lebanese food in town!
Excellent food and great service
Great food! Wonderful apetizers. Excellent service. Happy to visit again next time in Bethesda.
The service is great
Amazing. From the service to the delicious food.
Loved the Turkish coffee with cardamom, served with a piece of baklava.

The lunch was really tasty and very good pricing but the server was rude in some ways. He was upset that we didn’t get any drinks or desserts. You can tell from the impressions. Other than that we had a nice lunch.

Appetizers are delicious. Seriously the best eggplant appetizer I have had in the us.  Cheese filled fill was so fresh and delicious.   Maybe the best Lebanese restaurant in the area. Fish kabob was really good. I love tiger salad. Not to many items on the menu (which I like) , but good quality. Lunch special is great. One waiter takes care of customers alone, but surprisingly he is fast and does everything great. Thumbs up.  Edit: I visited today again, and shawarma was really really good. I give 4.5 stars.

Fantastic place to eat Lebanese food! Not too many restaurants offering true Lebanese food in this area, so this place is a real delight. Try ordering a few different appetizers so you can get a wider variety of food to sample from. We have had the kibbeh (comes with tahini) tabuleh, hummus,  foul (fava beans), and stuffed leaves. It is enough food for 2 people with a normal appetite. The tabuleh, although good, is not made to be the best. Traditionally, it should have all the herbs cut very very small and without stems. This restaurant could use more care in preparing the tabuleh. Also, the shawarmas are served open faced -- not traditional.  Aside from these little things, the cuisine is truly delicious and so delicate. Highly recommend eating here.  Please check their schedule since they close at 2pm and then reopen at 5 or 5.30pm for dinner.
The lemonade is a must have. But everything is great. True Lebanese food experience. Authentic.
If the weather is good, I recommend you to sit outside of the restaurant to see the sunset
Best Middle Eastern food in the D.C. area.

Food is delicious and comes out quickly. Highly recommend ordering tapas style so you can try lots of things on the menu. They definitely are not stingy with the bread, which I appreciate. The menu is pretty extensive and easily can accommodate any sort of dietary restrictions. The only downside is that it's a bit pricey, but that comes with the area.
Great food, great ambience, the prices are very reasonable, and the service is excellent!
(Translated by Google) Get the fat makdous entree !!!!  (Original) Get the fattet makdous entree!!!!

Waiters are great!!! Food was AMAZING and so flavorful!!! Definitely recommend their hummus, salmon, chicken shawarma, and stuffed grape leaves. Honestly everything we ordered was delicious and the dessert (a sort of pudding with baklava on the side) was perfection.

The service was great but most of the food was ok. Only one out of the three would have ordered the same thing again.  The dessert they recommended so highly (some sweet cheese thing)  was absolutely terrible, we each took one bite and left it. There was a big party in there that tripled the overall volume and ruined the ambiance. I really wanted to like this place but we don't plan on returning.
Good Lebanese food in a beautiful space at a reasonable price for Bethesda. Great place to take a girl on a date!
Food and service was amazing. I highly recommend
Great food, music, and setting overall
Nice ambiance. Good hummus and fatouxhe
Good food, good service
Only drawback is no halal but i dont eat meat anymore so everything elese is superb!
We had a lovely evening eating outside. She had a vegetarian sampler. I had lamb. Both were delicious. Service was pleasant and attentive. We'll go back.
Nice place with outdoor seating. Main course i had was ground beef stuffed in cabbage. Was rather salty, sour tasting, but maybe just my palate. Hummus and pita bread better.
Quick service and consistently good food. Highly recommend.
Middle Eastern cuisine, good variety, fresh food, delicious sharable dishes. Excellent service, prices moderate but good value for money.
Nice place
typical Lebanese food
Great food, good atmosphere. Coffee needs a to go cup.

Best service ever! We called ahead to let them know there were 15 of us. We got there and the tables were ready. I noticed that there was only ONE WAITER serving the already busy restaurant and thought "oh no!" We got seated and made our decisions for food. Shortly after, the lone waiter came to us quickly took our orders and started taking care of another large group. He was amazing! He took care of another 6-7 tables while he was attentive to our group and the large group. Food came out fast and friendly and right on time and we didn't want for anything. Oh and btw, the food was delicious!!  The whole operation was one guy waiting the tables and one or two guys in the kitchen!! It was amazing!!!  When he came with check, we gave the waiter a round of applause and thanked him appropriately for his excellent service.  If I could give this place and experience TEN STARS, I would!

(Translated by Google) I came for dinner with my husband and friends last week at Bacchus Bethesda. When we left, we were the last customers, I forgot my stole on my chair. I realized very quickly, we were in front of the restaurant saying goodbye to our friends. My husband immediately knocked on the door, it was closed. Not wanting to disturb anyone he called the next morning. No scarf in sight, hard to believe ... but hey ... we were advised to call back a week later to see if she had not left with the dirty laundry at the laundry. We recall and there we are told that if it was in the laundry it was automatically destroyed ... so this one had never been made to me before. We were also told, when we had not expressed this thought at all, being rather naively confident in the honesty of people on principle, that there was no thief in the staff .... If you go to this fairly expensive restaurant for good but not exceptional food and you care about your things, be very careful not to forget them. We, great lovers of Middle Eastern cuisine, will not be back.  (Original) Je suis venue diner avec mon mari et des amis la semaine dernière chez Bacchus Bethesda. En partant, nous etions les derniers clients, j'ai oublie mon étole sur ma chaise. Je m'en  suis tres vite aperçu, nous etions en face du restaurant entrain de dire au revoir à nos amis. Mon mari est allé frapper tout de suite à la porte, c'etait fermé. Ne voulant deranger personne il a appele le lendemain matin. Pas d'echarpe en vue, difficile à croire...mais bon...on nous a conseille de rappeler une semaine plus tard pour voir si elle n'etait pas partie avec le linge sale au pressing. Nous rappelons et là on nous dit que si elle etait au pressing elle a ete automatiquement detruite....alors celle-la on ne me l'avait encore jamais faite. On nous a dit aussi, alors que nous n'avions pas du tout emis cette pensee, etant plutot naivement confiant dans l'honneteté des gens par principe, qu'il n'y avait pas de voleur dans le personnel.... Si vous allez dans ce restaurant assez cher pour une cuisine bonne mais pas exceptionnelle et que vous tenez à vos affaires, faites tres attention de ne pas les y oublier. Nous , grands amateurs de cuisine moyen orientale, nous reviendrons pas.
Very romantic atmosphere nice plating. Only issue was slow service. But food was very authentic and fresh tasting.
Food came quickly and tasted really good! Went for dinner, and it was a little pricey but worth it.

So, I went here with a rather large group. I know that can be challenging. The food quality was excellent.  There was some confusion about the bill— someone had been charged twice for something.  It was a simple mistake that needed to be cleared up. They way the the man in charge handled it was inappropriate— rude, emotional, easily offended. Very poor display of customer service. His waitstaff seemed embarrassed and kept softly apologizing to us for the outburst.  They need to be organized about how to bill large tables. Have a policy, explain it clearly, stick to it. Treat humans graciously; you are in customer service after all.
This restaurant is beautiful with great food. The waiter was very kind and made sure we enjoyed our meal. The outside seating is great for summer nights.
Food was excellent; Fahoosh salad, chicken shwarma and hommus. Service was impressive.
16 year addict of bacchus.
The BEST patio in Bethesda for summer dining. Classic Lebanese food made well on a beautiful terrace with fountain and oversized umbrellas

We had a.company event at this restaurant, we all arrived at 7:45 and We ordered at 8:20 pm and and the food started to come out at 9:45 pm, we waited more than an hour and inquired about the food multiple time and the staff replied “it’s coming in minutes” every time we asked about it, the funny thing is that they close at 10 pm , they had two orders delivered at 10 pm and they had togo boxes coming out with them :( The food quality itself was ok , not great just ok
Really excellent middle Eastern food in Bethesda. Great out door space in warm weather.
Excellent
Long standing restaurant provides great food
Always great food and very authentic!! Tastes just like my Mom's cooking!
Great good and service.
Food and service are both outstanding! Highly recommended!!!
Great food, great service, great ambiance. One of our favorite restaurants in Bethesda!
Great food and atmosphere and service
Great food and service! Highly recommend it if you are a fan of this food!
The best real Labanees resturnat in DC area. defiantly beef shawerma is the best
Yummy

Over the years I have taken a lot of friends and business associates to Bacchus. They have all been impressed. We often stick with appetizers and order a variety to share. I  highly recommend this restaurant.
Excellent Mideast cusine

Excellent dinner experience, there were so many good options in the menu that I preferred ask the waiter to surprise me, and he did it far more than I expected... I’ve tasted Lebanese food right in the source and here I’ve enjoyed the closest experience that’s related not only to the food but to the service as well.

Been here with my wife twice for dinner in 2 consecutive nights. 5 stars service for both nights. 4 stars for food. 5 stars for ambiance. 5 stars for prices as they have special price for weekdays dinner.
Great food and ambience!  Very authentic, reminds me of homemade.  A must try for my fellow Lebanese foodies.

The food is good, but it always feel it was prepared a couple of days ago. The salads and meat are fresh, but the mezze (hummus, Baba ghanouj, etc...) taste like they were in the fridge for a while. They are still good but not fresh.
The antithesis of the trendy modern restaurant.  Low key and great food and staff.  And, they really care about their customers!  A rare gem!
Very friendly and fresh food and friendly. Very hospitable

The food was excellent.  We ordered several different appetizers instead of  entrees so we could sample a little of everything.  Very fresh. The dessert was very delicious too. The service was excellent.  Several different servers make sure your drinks are always filled. Very pleasant conversations with the staff. I would eat here again.

I do not recomend it. The resturant was very smelly. The waiter was so rude and unprofessional when we asked him to change the table because of the unpleasant smell. Two members of our family got sick after eaten their food. If you care about your health do not go there.
Always amazing with very authentic food. Small and cozy with perfect ambiance.
Food is great....service is amazing.....our server was very attentive and sweet.
I have enjoyed Bacchus Lebanon of over years...Consistent with great service and wonderful Lebanese food. I always go back.

This place is great if you are not black. My husband and I went there a few years back before we had children and it was very clear that they did not want us there. One female waitress stomped to the kitchen looking upset that we where there. They sat us near the kitchen/bathroom away from everyone and that same waitress looked appalled that I used their restroom. Our waiter seemed nice enough but you could tell they sent the one waiter who would tolerate us. When it was time to leave the hostess said something and my husband said to her we know you do not want us here. It was raining outside so my husband wanted me to stand near the door while he pulled the car up. The hostess did not like that and almost told me I could not stand there or to leave but she caught herself and just stood there uncomfortable. The funny thing is there is lots of Lebanese in my country, which is an African country so I thought they would be cool. I give one star because the food was good.

This is the best Lebonese in DC let alone the East Coast.  Always spot on the food is phenomenal, outdoor seating at Bethesda is unheard of. Absolutely authentic and delicious, this is coming from a Lebanese guy who knows how to eat.
The best middle eastern resturant in DC area!!!!!!
We take friends here because the food is special, wait service tops, and menu  outstanding. The owner appreciates your loyalty and may show it with a small free desert.

The waiter was great, helping us select from the unfamiliar foods. Everything was so very good that I now feel Lebanese food is among my favorite. A single visit made me a big fan. Well worth the moderately high prices.
Outstanding selection of delicious food.  Much much better than Lebanese taverna.  More authentic and more family style.  Can't be beat for Lebanese food in dc/md/va area
Not the best food...
One of my family's all time favorite restaurants.   Great food and great staff.

Love this place. I would recommend to do mezza style. It is like a tappaz style. This place has 12 freaking page menu, the only way to discover the menu is to get a lots of small dishes. Me and my wife usually do 6-8 appetizers and sometimes it is fun to dig in to leftovers the next day.
Amazing staff, delicious food. If you go during warmer months they have the patio open. It's in a convenient location and I have yet to have a bad meal here.

Amazing place! We had my grandmothers 95th birthday celebration here. We are of middle eastern background and everyone absolutely loved the food. Service is top notch! The owner and his staff make you feel as though you are his special guests. Appetizers are delicious and you can make an entire meal out of all the choices. We have been back numerous times and the consistency of the food and service is always stellar!
Quality Lebanese food. Great lunch special.
Service was a bit slow, but the food was delicious.
Love this place: delicious food, helpful staff, and relaxing outdoor seating.
Very nice Lebanese restaurant.  The food is very good, the atmosphere congenial and the outdoor patio is a wonderful place for a leisurely dinner with family and friends in the summer.
Weird atmosphere but food was delicious and traditional.

I have been going to Bacchus for almost 30 years.  Insofar as classical middle Eastern food I think it is hard to beat.  It is easy to make a meal out of the long list of appetizers, which can easily be shared.  I suggest ordering an assortment of appetizers and then you can get some kabobs for the main course.  The waiters are good at suggesting things, don't hesitate to ask.  The décor is nothing special - however the food and service (and price) are what makes we return time after time.  Our friends from the Middle East have confirmed the authenticity and high quality of the food, on many occasions.
I have been going to the restaurant for years. They have the best appetizers and best food around the D.M.V area. The service is spectacular , try it and you will love it.

We have been to Bacchus of Lebanon many times. The food and service have always been exquisite. Here is the the short part of the review: step #1 - find the manager( or owner if there are in that day), step #2 tell them what you like to eat or if there are any dietary needs, step #3 - let them pair your meal with the beer or wine, step #4 - enjoy a fantastic experience. Here is the long part of this review. We have been to Bacchus during the day for late lunch. We have been to Bacchus during late dinner while they had a very large family gathering. We have been to Bacchus during the normal dinner hours. We have never had anything but fantastic, attentive service. The staff at Bacchus is friendly and welcoming. They are happy to share stories and talk about from where the food or wine comes. We have brought several friends and all of them have raved about the experience. The food and pairings are always on point, mixing interesting and familiar flavors. Please take the time to enjoy this gem of culture you will not be disappointed.

I've met here with different friends twice recently (balmy evenings in July and August 2014, which is unusual for this area), have eaten outdoors.  The atmosphere in the outdoor part of the restaurant is wonderful, and the food is predictably yummy  -- and reasonably priced. Both evenings were unusually pleasant and seemed like time out of time -- no feeling of nearby hustle and bustle.

We had dinner @ Bacchus one cold winter night and came out all warm and full! Service is a bit of a sore point here with this being a very family run restaurant, roles often get overlapped and that ends up with lower service levels than a bigger chain.  But the food makes up for the poor service. They have an extensive menu that takes some time going thru and the decision making is that much harder given the excellent choices in the menu!  The Hummus and Labneh were good appetizer choices that everyone liked.  We ordered the following for the main course and here is my review of the dishes that I tasted/ had as my main course: Combination (Extraordinaire Bacchus) - The lamb in the Shish Kebab was tender, and succulent and seasoned well  Warak Inab Mehchi - the minced meat was flavorful and cooked well in the grape leaf that had a nice tang to it.  The portions are huge, especially if you order appetizers and we had enough left for a decent meal portion the next day!  They do have a decent selection of wines to go with the food :)
The appetizers were good but the main course was overcooked. Service was average, nice ambiance though.

Bacchus is one of my favorite restaurants in Bethesda.  The interior is warm and welcoming and the outdoor seating is shaded and pleasant with a fountain to soften the sounds of the street.  The food is excellent.  I've enjoyed every dish and appetizer I've tried, and I've tried several of them.  It's a great spot to walk to for lunch, sit outside, and enjoy a delicious lunch before returning to the office.

A favorite lunch get-away with my husband, Bacchus feels like leaving the country for a meal. We love the atmosphere, the food is delicious, the portions are generous and the lunch prices can't be beat ($12 for 2 courses!) The meal is made fresh so it's definitely not "fast food", but we always find it well worth the wait.
